**Waypoint Math**

For same-cell movement, `moveSeg.m_cellA == moveSeg.m_cellB`, so:

```cpp
resetPos = moveSeg.getBegin(moveSeg.m_cellB)
```

at [CollisionResolve.cpp:320](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/sha
red/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:320) is just previous-frame position `A`. `getBegin`, `getEnd`, and 
`atParam` are:

```cpp
begin = getBegin(relativeCell);
end = getEnd(relativeCell);
return begin + (end-begin)*time;
```

at [CollisionResolve.cpp:40](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shar
ed/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:40)-[70](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision
/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:70).

Resolution builds `positions` like this:

```cpp
contactPoint = moveSeg.atParam(contactCell, contact.m_time);
outList.push_back(CellPosition(contactCell, contactPoint));
...
delta = secondSeg.getDelta(contactCell);
slidDelta = Collision3d::SingleSlide(delta, contact.m_normal);
...
moveSeg.m_pointA = contactPoint;
moveSeg.m_pointB = contactPoint + slidDelta;
```

at [CollisionResolve.cpp:421](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/sha
red/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:421)-[463](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollis
ion/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:463). If the next iteration finds no contact, it appends 
the slide endpoint at [CollisionResolve.cpp:389](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/shar
edCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:389)-[401](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/l
ibrary/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:401). Replay is 
`setPosition_p(resetPos)` then `moveObjectAlong(objectA, positions)` at [CollisionResolve.cpp:337](D:
/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:33
7)-[339](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionRes
olve.cpp:339).

Let `D = B - A`, `t = circleHitTime`.

If slide is stopped/canceled, final is `A + tD`.

If slide survives, final is `A + tD + SingleSlide((1-t)D, N)`. `SingleSlide` projects out the inward 
normal component and preserves tangent/binormal components at [CollisionUtils.cpp:249](D:/Code/swg-cl
ient-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionUtils.cpp:249)-[315](D:/Co
de/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionUtils.cpp:315). 
It is a proper tangential slide.

For `t ~= 0.0`: contact-only final is `A`, so from attempted `B` it looks like `-D`. With slide 
retained, final is `A + SingleSlide(D,N)`, i.e. tangential movement only.

For `t ~= 0.7`: contact-only final is `A + 0.7D`. That is forward relative to previous frame by 
`+0.7D`, but backward relative to the attempted endpoint by `-0.3D`. With slide retained, final is 
`A + 0.7D + projected(0.3D)`. The code rejects a slide whose dot against original movement is 
non-forward: [CollisionResolve.cpp:448](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollisi
on/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:448)-[454](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sh
aredCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:454). So a `min ~= 0.7` contact should not move 
behind the previous position; it is a visible backward correction from the already-applied target 
`B`, not net backward from `A`.

**Detection vs Resolution**

`resolveCollisions`/`findFirstContact` does not distinguish “center walked ok, circle grazed” from 
“center blocked.” By the time the contact reaches `findContactWithFloor`, `centerWalkResult` has 
been collapsed into `PWR_HitEdge` plus hit tri/edge/time/normal. The asymmetry is in detection: the 
filter at [FloorMesh.cpp:2838](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/sh
ared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2838)-[2840](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/
src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2840) only constrains circle hits when center result is `ExitedMesh`, 
`HitPortalEdge`, or `HitEdge`; it excludes `PWR_WalkOk`. Then the FWD branch records a hard contact 
without the PEN branch’s `wallEpsilon` gate at [FloorMesh.cpp:2911](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/
shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2911)-[2916](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/e
ngine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2916).

Narrower safe fix: detection, at the FWD circle-contact record around [FloorMesh.cpp:2913](D:/Code/sw
g-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2913), gated 
specifically for `centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk` circle-only grazes. That preserves normal wall 
blocking where the center hits/contacts an edge and avoids changing global slide response in 
`CollisionResolve`, which affects all extents, floors, obstacles, and multi-contact sliding.
