For `t ~= 0.0`: contact-only final is `A`, so from attempted `B` it looks like `-D`. With slide retained, final is `A + SingleSlide(D,N)`, i.e. tangential movement only.

For `t ~= 0.7`: contact-only final is `A + 0.7D`. That is forward relative to previous frame by `+0.7D`, but backward relative to the attempted endpoint by `-0.3D`. With slide retained, final is `A + 0.7D + projected(0.3D)`. The code rejects a slide whose dot against original movement is non-forward: [CollisionResolve.cpp:448](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:448)-[454](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:454). So a `min ~= 0.7` contact should not move behind the previous position; it is a visible backward correction from the already-applied target `B`, not net backward from `A`.

**Detection vs Resolution**

`resolveCollisions`/`findFirstContact` does not distinguish “center walked ok, circle grazed” from “center blocked.” By the time the contact reaches `findContactWithFloor`, `centerWalkResult` has been collapsed into `PWR_HitEdge` plus hit tri/edge/time/normal. The asymmetry is in detection: the filter at [FloorMesh.cpp:2838](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2838)-[2840](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2840) only constrains circle hits when center result is `ExitedMesh`, `HitPortalEdge`, or `HitEdge`; it excludes `PWR_WalkOk`. Then the FWD branch records a hard contact without the PEN branch’s `wallEpsilon` gate at [FloorMesh.cpp:2911](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2911)-[2916](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2916).

Narrower safe fix: detection, at the FWD circle-contact record around [FloorMesh.cpp:2913](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2913), gated specifically for `centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk` circle-only grazes. That preserves normal wall blocking where the center hits/contacts an edge and avoids changing global slide response in `CollisionResolve`, which affects all extents, floors, obstacles, and multi-contact sliding.
